igiösen Institutionen suchen sie auf ihre spezifische Weise Lebenssinn zu generieren. Insoweit sind sie selbst zentrale Akteure der modernen Religionsgeschichte.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aReligion and the social sciencesvCongresses. 0aReligionxPhilosophyxHistoryy19th centuryvCongresses. 0aReligionxPhilosophyxHistoryy20th centuryvCongresses. 4aHistorisches Kolleg. 4aIntellektuelle. 4aIntellektuellengeschichte. 4aModerne Religionsgeschichte. 4aReformbewegungen. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aArnold, Claus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraf, Friedrich Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraf, Friedrich Wilhelm, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHaury, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHübinger, Gangolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKracht, Klaus Große, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrech, Volkhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller-Luckner, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNottmeier, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReuter, Astrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSieg, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI0 cprintz978348658257440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110446364